2005-08-14 13:07:08  Rev 7417   josef

	* ggz-kde/po/kggz.pot ggz-kde/po/de.po:
	  - German translation update
	  - make myself translator again


2005-08-14 09:47:25  Rev 7406   josef

	* ggz-kde/src/KGGZ.cpp ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.h 
	  ggz-kde/src/widgets/KGGZUsers.cpp ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.cpp:
	  - finish the improved seat assignment dialog
	  - chat bots and buddies are now read for real
	  This is really complicated:
	  game host -> player, with name, not changeable
	  reservation -> normal registration, with name
	  buddy -> like reservation, but displayed in extra list
	  bot -> bot seat, without name
	  named bot -> bot seat, with name
	  chat bot -> normal registration, with name, but displayed as bot


2005-08-14 08:13:55  Rev 7405   josef

	* ggz-kde/src/KGGZ.cpp ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.h 
	  ggz-kde/data/icons/players/Makefile.am 
	  ggz-kde/data/icons/players/botgrubby.png ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.cpp:
	  - improved launch dialog
	  - prepare possibility to add grubbies as "named bots" too
	  Grubbies can only be added if they're in the current room, as they
	  are not registered with the game server (anybody can run one).
	  The problem for KGGZ is to find out which games are supported by
	  grubby.
	  Then, if grubby sees a table launch where there's a seat reserved
	  for him, he should join automatically, the the "/join my game" 
	  command
	  becomes superfluous.


2005-08-13 22:24:02  Rev 7402   josef

	* ggz-kde/ggzcore++/src/GGZCoreGametype.cpp ggz-kde/src/KGGZ.cpp 
	  ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.h ggz-kde/ggzcore++/src/GGZCoreGametype.h 
	  ggz-kde/src/KGGZLaunch.cpp:
	  - cross-module change: named bots (server->client part)
	  - implemented parsing [NamedBots] sections from game .dsc file
	  - those values are transmitted to the client
	  - ggzcore parses it and puts it into its gametype info
	  - ggzcore++ has accessors to them
	  - kggz can read the entries and display them in the launch dialog


